meanings.definition: Print (something) in addition to the usual number or quantity.
meanings.sent1: She overprinted more flyers for the event to ensure everyone got one.
meanings.sent2: The company overprinted extra copies of the report for distribution.
meanings.sent3: The printer accidentally overprinted so many copies that the room was filled with paper.
meanings.sent4: Her enthusiasm for the project overprinted any doubts she had about its success.
meanings.sent5: The artist's signature was overprinted in bold red, making it stand out.

meanings.definition: Print (something) on top of an existing print.
meanings.sent1: He carefully overprinted the logo on the letterhead to create a watermark effect.
meanings.sent2: The designer decided to overprint the text on the image for a unique look.
meanings.sent3: The cat walked across the freshly overprinted document, leaving paw prints everywhere.
meanings.sent4: His memories of the past overprinted the present moment, creating a sense of nostalgia.
meanings.sent5: The rain overprinted the ink on the paper, causing the colors to blend together.
